# LLDB tuning for on-device debug attach speed.
#
# The default behavior is to read symbols for every loaded image from the
# device's memory before letting the app continue past `main()`. With Supabase
# + RevenueCat + AppsFlyer + PostHog + Lottie + a DAM extension, that's many
# thousands of Swift type symbols round-tripped over USB on attach — exactly
# what produces the "Launching ... is taking longer than expected. LLDB is
# likely reading from device memory to resolve symbols." dialog.
#
# These settings defer symbol load until something actually needs them
# (breakpoint, backtrace, `po`, crash). Cold launch becomes ~seconds instead
# of minutes; breakpoints still work, you just pay the symbol cost on first
# hit per image.

# Don't read symbols for every loaded library on attach.
settings set target.preload-symbols false

# Load Swift symbol tables on demand (per image, when needed).
settings set symbols.load-on-demand true

# Skip the kernel-extension scan that doesn't apply to iOS apps anyway.
settings set plugin.dynamic-loader.darwin-kernel.scan-type none
